description: This landscape cross stitch pattern entitled London Bridge shows the bridge spanning the longest river in England famously known as the Thames River.  The bridge is actually called the Tower Bridge, but most people know this iconic image as London Bridge.  No blended colors are used in our patterns.  We only use an abundance of solid colors as it produces a more realistic effect.  Only full cross stitches are used in our designs. Stitch Count: 252w x 189h Fabric: Aida, Antique White  Four approximate finished sizes: 14,16,18 and 22 Count Final Pattern Sizes: 14 Count, 18w X 13-1/2h in 16 Count, 15-3/4w X 11-3/4h in 18 Count, 14w X 10-1/2h in 22 Count, 11-3/8w X 8-1/2h in   *Please Note: The above dimensions do not include frame or mat. Number of Colors Used: 116What you will receive!!! Our patterns arrive with a color visual photo of finished design, wash and care instructions, handy tips for working the pattern, instruction sheet detailing color of fabric, sizes, a complete color listing including number of skeins to purchase.
